 \sum_{j = i + 1}^n \frac{1}{j - i + 1} 
 \sum_{k=1}^{n - i} \frac{1}{k + 1} 
k=j-i
j=i+1
j-i=1
k=1
j=n
k=j-i=n-i
j-i=k
 \sum_{j -i = 1}^n \frac{1}{j - i + 1}\\ \text{Let $j-i=k$, giving }\sum_{k=1}^{n-i} \frac{1}{k + 1}
\sum_{j = i + 1}^n \frac{1}{j - i + 1}
=\frac{1}{2}+...+\frac{1}{n-i+1}
=\sum_{k=1}^{n - i} \frac{1}{k + 1}
